Problem : Reverse a Linkedln List
Given the head of a linked list, the task is to reverse this list and return the reversed head.

Examples:

Input: head: 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> NULL
Output: head: 4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 1 -> NULL
ğŸ§  Concept Behind:
A singly linked list only points forward, so we need to manually reverse the .next pointer of each node to point backward.
This must be done without using extra space (in-place reversal).

âœ… Approach: Iterative Pointer Manipulation
We use three pointers:

curr â†’ Current node in traversal

prev â†’ Node that comes before current (initially null)

temp â†’ Used to store curr.next temporarily (to not lose track)

ğŸ” Step-by-Step Execution:
Assume list: 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> null

Initialization:
prev = null

curr = head (1)

Iteration 1:
temp = curr.next â†’ 2

curr.next = prev â†’ 1.next = null

prev = curr â†’ 1

curr = temp â†’ 2

List: 1 -> null, now move to 2

Iteration 2:
temp = 3

2.next = 1

prev = 2

curr = 3

List: 2 -> 1 -> null

Repeat until curr == null, and return prev (which is now head of reversed list)

ğŸ“Œ Final Java Code:

class Solution {
    Node reverseList(Node head) {
        Node curr = head;
        Node prev = null;

        while (curr != null) {
            Node temp = curr.next;  // Step 1
            curr.next = prev;       // Step 2
            prev = curr;            // Step 3
            curr = temp;            // Step 4
        }

        return prev; // New head
    }
}
â± Time & Space Complexity:
Type	Complexity
Time Complexity	O(n)
Space Complexity	O(1)

âœ… In-place algorithm
âœ… Efficient for large linked lists

